OL,3,CChorley MP says local elections should
OL,4,Cgo ahead, despite council position
OL,6,FWords by Senior Westminster Producer
OL,7,FLili Donlon-Mansbridge
OL,9,FThe Speaker of the House of Commons,
OL,10,FSir Lindsay Hoyle, told a councillor
OL,11,Fthat he thinks the local elections in
OL,12,FChorley this May should go ahead, ITV
OL,13,FNews can reveal.
OL,15,FChorley Borough Council, which is run
OL,16,Fby Labour, is among several councils
OL,17,Fthat have written to the government
OL,18,Frequesting that their elections in May
OL,19,Fbe postponed. A third of seats on the
OL,20,Fcouncil were due to be up for election.
