OL,3,CChorley MP says local elections should
OL,4,Cgo ahead, despite council position
OL,6,FAsked by a Reform Lancashire county
OL,7,Fcouncillor if he would "seek
OL,8,Fassurances" from the chief executive
OL,9,Fand leader of Chorley Council that
OL,10,Felections would not be delayed, Hoyle
OL,11,Fwrote he had made his views "clearly
OL,12,Fknown to the leader of the Council."
OL,14,FHoyle acknowledged that, despite his
OL,15,Fviews, he "understood the arguments
OL,16,Fmade for postponing elections" during
OL,17,Flocal government reorganisation and
OL,18,Fthat it was up to Chorley Council to
OL,19,Fdetermine their own position.
