OL,3,CChorley MP says local elections should
OL,4,Cgo ahead, despite council position
OL,6,F"Whilst I understand the arguments
OL,7,Fmade for postponing elections given
OL,8,Fthe fact that wholesale change will be
OL,9,Fimplemented in the next 12 months, I
OL,10,Fdo not believe in cancelling elections
OL,11,Fand personally believe that the local
OL,12,Felections on May 2026 should take
OL,13,Fplace," he wrote.
OL,15,F"I have made these views clearly known
OL,16,Fto the Leader of the Council. However,
OL,17,Fthis is not a decision I can make. It
OL,18,Fis for the council in Chorley to
OL,19,Fdetermine its own actions and explain
OL,20,Ftheir position accordingly to the
OL,21,Fpublic."
