OL,6,FHoyle has been the MP for Chorley
OL,7,Fsince 1997. He was previously elected
OL,8,Fas a Labour MP, but has been
OL,9,Fpolitically neutral since he took up
OL,10,Fthe role of Speaker of the House of
OL,11,FCommons in November 2019.
OL,13,FThe Speaker of the House is elected by
OL,14,FMPs at the start of every new
OL,15,Fparliament. The roles include
OL,16,Foverseeing the debate and rules of the
OL,17,FHouse of Commons. It is a politically
OL,18,Fimpartial role.
