OL,6,FThe leader of Chorley Council, Cllr
OL,7,FAlistair Bradley told a meeting about
OL,8,Fthe decision in November that
OL,9,Fproceeding with elections "would throw
OL,10,Fa huge spanner" into the process of
OL,11,Freorganisation.
OL,13,FChorley Council is expected to be part
OL,14,Fof a significant restructuring
OL,15,Fdetermined by central government,
OL,16,Fwhich could see it merge with nearby
OL,17,FSouth Ribble and West Lancashire to
OL,18,Fform a new council area.
