OL,3,CChorley MP says local elections should
OL,4,Cgo ahead, despite council position
OL,6,FWhilst I understand the arguments made
OL,7,Ffor postponing elections given the
OL,8,Ffact that wholesale change will be
OL,9,Fimplemented in the next 12 months, I
OL,10,Fdo not believe in cancelling elections
OL,11,Fand personally believe that the local
OL,12,Felections on May 2026 should take
OL,13,Fplace. I have made these views clearly
OL,14,Fknown to the Leader of the Council.
OL,15,FHowever, this is not a decision I can
OL,16,Fmake. It is for the council in Chorley
OL,17,Fto determine its own actions and
OL,18,Fexplain their position accordingly to
OL,19,Fthe public.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/17
